{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Persist ticket digest as a REVIEW_RESULT-style sidecar (shared cache)\n\n## Why\nThe digest is a billable LLM artifact we never want to recompute (~$1.90 to enrich the whole 793-ticket store â€” see epic experiment comment). Storing it in the SHARED store (auto-pushed) makes one client's enrichment a cache-hit for everyone. rebar's exact precedent is `REVIEW_RESULT`: a reducer-IGNORED, preserved-and-ignored, per-ticket LLM-derived sidecar with a schema sentinel + a `prune` retention. We mirror it.\n\n## What â€” payload schema (fully specified)\nA `TICKET_DIGEST` sidecar event. Its `data` payload:\n`{\"schema\": \"ticket_digest_v1\", \"digest\": {problem_keywords, component_or_area, key_entities, propositions}, \"content_hash\": \"<hex>\", \"model\": \"<model-id>\", \"digest_hash_version\": <int>}`.\nThe `schema` sentinel `\"ticket_digest_v1\"` guards reads (mirrors REVIEW_RESULT keying on `payload['schema'] == 'plan_review_result_v1'`) so a foreign/older payload is skipped, not mis-parsed. `content_hash`, `model`, `digest_hash_version` are the three freshness tags (named fields in the payload).\n\n## Content hash â€” REUSE the canonical normalizer (no reinvented normalization)\n`content_hash = sha256(_ticket_text(state))` where `_ticket_text` is the EXISTING canonical join in `src/rebar/_engine_support/gates.py:30` (title + description + comment bodies, `\"\\n\".join`). We do NOT define a new normalization â€” divergence from what S1 hashed would silently mis-mark freshness. `DIGEST_HASH_VERSION` (module constant in the digest sidecar) is bumped only if the hashed field-set ever changes, invalidating all cached digests deterministically.\n\n## Freshness (computed on read, fail-closed)\nThe digest is CURRENT iff ALL of: stored `content_hash` == `sha256(_ticket_text(current))`, stored `model` == active model, stored `digest_hash_version` == current constant. Any mismatch â†’ stale. If current state can't be read (partial read) â†’ NOT-current (fail-closed; never falsely fresh).\n\n## Scope (exact edit targets â€” every registry a new event type touches)\n- `src/rebar/_store/event_append.py`: add `\"TICKET_DIGEST\"` to the `EVENT_TYPES` write allow-list AND its enumerated string in the StoreError message (lines ~97-103).\n- `src/rebar/reducer/_version.py`: add `\"TICKET_DIGEST\"` to `_NON_REPLAY_KNOWN_TYPES` (NOT `KNOWN_EVENT_TYPES`) â€” preserved-and-ignored, never compacted into SNAPSHOT, no fsck WARN (mirrors REVIEW_RESULT).\n- New `src/rebar/llm/overlap/__init__.py` (the package) + `src/rebar/llm/overlap/digest_sidecar.py` with `emit(digest, ticket_id)` (appends + calls `prune`), `prune(ticket_id, keep=1)`, `latest_ticket_digest(ticket_id)` (guards on the `ticket_digest_v1` sentinel) â€” all modeled on `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/sidecar.py`.\n- `show` freshness render (two-part, explicit): `src/rebar/_engine_support/reads.py::show_state` ATTACHES a `digest_freshness` field (\"present-fresh\"|\"present-stale\"|\"absent\") to the returned state dict by calling `latest_ticket_digest` + the freshness check; `src/rebar/reducer/_present.py` RENDERS that field in `show` output. Only the flag is shown, never the raw digest text (no new field in `ticket_state.schema.json`; sidecar, like REVIEW_RESULT).\n- Prune invocation: `emit` calls `prune(keep=1)` on every write (REVIEW_RESULT pattern); additionally a digest whose ticket is archived/deleted is dropped lazily when `latest_ticket_digest` observes the ticket is gone.\n\n## Dependencies\nS1 (indecisive-callous-armyworm) â€” produces the `ticket_digest` payload. (The drain that decides to re-enrich lives in S4; this story owns only WRITE + READ + freshness of the sidecar, not the skip decision.)\n\n## Testing\n- `tests/unit/test_ticket_digest_store.py`: `test_roundtrip`; `test_freshness_all_triggers` (stale on content-hash OR model OR digest_hash_version change); `test_hash_parity` (this ticket's `content_hash` == S1's over shared fixtures via `_ticket_text`); `test_fail_closed` (unreadable â†’ not-current); `test_latest_wins` (two appends, latest-by-HLC); `test_older_binary_ignores` (fsck no WARN); `test_show_render`; `test_prune_archived`.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `TICKET_DIGEST` writeâ†’`latest_ticket_digest` read roundtrip with the `ticket_digest_v1` sentinel guard; `pytest ...::test_roundtrip`.\n- [ ] Freshness flips stale on ANY of content-hash / model / digest_hash_version mismatch; `::test_freshness_all_triggers`. content_hash uses `_ticket_text` (parity with S1); `::test_hash_parity`.\n- [ ] `TICKET_DIGEST` in `EVENT_TYPES` + `_NON_REPLAY_KNOWN_TYPES` (not `KNOWN_EVENT_TYPES`); older binary preserves-and-ignores, no fsck WARN; `::test_older_binary_ignores`.\n- [ ] Unreadable current state â†’ NOT-current (fail-closed); `::test_fail_closed`.\n- [ ] `show` renders digest presence + freshness (not raw text); `::test_show_render`. Archived ticket's digest pruned; `::test_prune_archived`.\n"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783625677546229001,"uuid":"49fec095-84fb-432e-9d03-ea8bd72df1e8"}